THE Wellness Healthcare Group has said it is set to inaugurate the Pharmacentre app which will improve healthcare delivery through the supply of medical and laboratory test kits. The group disclosed this in a statement in Lagos on Sunday, adding that the software was designed as a framework to make pharmaceutical products accessible to individuals. The statement read, “The Pharmacentre app is a business-to-business and business-to-customer software platform created by Wellness Medical Distribution to leverage technology in the distribution of medical supplies, pharmaceutical products, laboratory test kits, and reagents to hospitals, pharmacies, laboratories, patent medicine stores, and individuals at competitive prices, with a framework to make life easy for everyone in the health sector and the world at large. “The app is a multi-vendor, integrative pharma commerce platform for pharmaceutical logistics uniting pharmacies, distributors, wholesalers, retailers and end-users. Its mission is to ease the supply chain and bottlenecks that typify access to pharma products. “WHG is passionate about delivering quality healthcare and improving healthcare delivery and they do this through affordable and seamless services which impact the promotion of general well-being.”  All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com